sentence: Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG) has been named as a Top 25 ''Dividend Giant'' by ETF Channel, with a staggering $33.59B worth of stock held by ETFs, and above-average ''DividendRank'' statistics including a strong 2.66% yield, according to the most recent Dividend Channel ''DividendRank'' report.
The report noted a strong quarterly dividend history at Procter & Gamble Company , and favorable long-term multi-year growth rates in key fundamental data points.
The annualized dividend paid by Procter & Gamble Company is $3.1628/share, currently paid in quarterly installments, and its most recent dividend ex-date was on 04/23/2020.
Below is a long-term dividend history chart for PG, which the report stressed as being of key importance.
Indeed, studying a company's past dividend history can be of good help in judging whether the most recent dividend is likely to continue.
